{
  "text": "Thiocoraline, a depsipeptide bisintercalator with potent antitumor activity and antibiotic activity against Gram-positive bacteria, was first isolated from the mycelial cake of a marine actinomycete strain L-13-ACM2-092, Micromonospora marina [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It has shown antineoplastic activity against human cancer cells, such as Jin Jin and Yujia Zhao have contributed equally to this work.",
